1. useradd -m -G wheel -s /bin/bash xsaya 
2. passwd xsaya
3. EDITOR=vim visudo -> #%wheel ALL=(ALL) ALL
                        ^remove
4. exit root, login xsaya                         
5. sudo pacman -Syu
6. sudo pacman -S xorg-xerver xorg-xinit nvidia(libglvnd if asked) \
        pipewire pipewire-alsa pipewire-pulse wireplumber(connection logic)
(pipewire-pulse needed, many system applications still send out calls to PulseAudio)
                alternatively use the old ways of ->  pulseaudio \
                    i3-wm i3blocks(maybe not needed)
                            kitty (fallback terminal)

7. reboot, login xsaya (must reboot for audio services to start (hopefully automatically))
8. startx /usr/bin/i3, choose alt as $mod -> open terminal in i3
9. git clone https://github.com/vsaya/dotfiles.git (currently needs key to authenticate)
10. cd dotfiles -> stow
11. cd .stow-local-ignore -> ./bootstrap (the bootstrap script installs the rest of the system)
12. done 
